{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a7e35e97-1bd6-430a-be1c-50e0b8da0dd2","content":"This is a known MTP behavioral difference. In MTP, **exit code 8** means \"no tests were discovered.\" VSTest returned 0 in that case.\n\n**Two ways to fix it:**\n\n### Option 1 – CI pipeline (recommended)\n\nPass `--ignore-exit-code 8` to your `dotnet test` command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --ignore-exit-code 8\n```\n\n### Option 2 – Environment variable\n\nSet `TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8` in your CI environment so all test invocations ignore the \"zero tests\" exit code.\n\n### Option 3 – Project-level (MSBuild property)\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to apply one of these fixes to your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"435ee621-c446-4a26-9436-877f66e5278c","outputTokens":239,"requestId":"287A:DCED6:15EA87F:1754C45:6A046036"},"id":"d5b6a2ad-707c-469b-ab78-4d57ea325b83","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:27:56.488Z","parentId":"0cc2c884-e0b2-4b40-8fc8-f04180a5c42c"}
